'''Scott Grix''' (born 1 May 1984 in [[Halifax, West Yorkshire|Halifax]]) is an Irish professional [[rugby league]] footballer for [[Huddersfield Giants|Huddersfield]] of [[Super League]]. The former Ireland national team captain, he played throughout the backline previously with [[Halifax RLFC|Halifax]] (twice), [[Doncaster RLFC|Doncaster]],  [[Limoux Grizzlies|Limoux]], [[Warrington Wolves|Warrington]], [[Leigh Centurions|Leigh]], [[Widnes Vikings|Widnes]] and [[Wakefield Trinity Wildcats|Wakefield Trinity]]. He is the older brother of [[Simon Grix]], who plays for [[Warrington Wolves|Warrington]].

Currently, Scott is shining for Huddersfield. He was awarded the Supporters' Player of the Year in 2011. 
Scott had a brilliant season in 2012 and 2013 and will, hopefully, continue to be a quality player for the Huddersfield Giants in 2014.

==International career==
Grix is an [[Ireland national rugby league team|Irish]] international, making his d<U+00E9>but in 2006 against [[Russia national rugby league team|Russia]].<ref name="Scott Grix">{{cite web|url=http://www.widnesvikings.co.uk/players.php?id=11|title=Scott Grix|publisher=Widnes|date=2007-07-20|accessdate=2007-07-20 |archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20070927201412/http://www.widnesvikings.co.uk/players.php?id=11 <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2007-09-27}}</ref> He was named as captain of the [[2008 Rugby League World Cup squads#Ireland|Ireland]] squad for the [[2008 Rugby League World Cup]], and was one of his countries better players in the tournament.<ref name="Cassidy included in Ireland squad">{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/rugby_league/7657596.stm|title=Cassidy included in Ireland squad|publisher=BBC|date=2008-10-07|accessdate=2008-10-07}}</ref>

He later relinquished the captaincy to [[Liam Finn (rugby league)|Liam Finn]], however he continued to feature for Ireland and was named in their squad for the [[2013 Rugby League World Cup]].

